column3: BTW, no need to open a new pull every time you change something, you can just (force-)push to the same branch on github.\n
Thank you, I squashed to 1 commit.\n

BTW; adding a few sanity-check unit tests here was good, however just for info the majority of testing RPC functionality happens in the Python RPC tests in `qa/rpc-tests`. It's easier to do there as it is possible to spin up extra nodes, simulate a network of nodes, etc.\n
